			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Question... I have a 66 Bst main that I've been playing and, due partially to OoW, have gotten quite tired of LFG 3 hours a day and fighting 3 mobs before the group disbands or wipes. I was thinking of levelling my bard alt to 65+, making it my 3rd 65+ char (have a 65 Wiz as well).
<br />

<br />
Anyone have any opinions whether it would be worth it or not? I like my bard so far, and aside from my epic/LotH/Ornate boots I'm geared till 66+. I figured at least he would be helpful on guild raids and the like, possibly become a regularly played toon while I let my Bst retire for a few months.
<br />

<br />
Feel free to give me any tips, opinions or comments. I could use them.
<br />

<br />
P.S.; toon is new, I am not. I started EQ when the Tunare server first opened 5+ years ago</span></td>
