				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a 52 bl and 65 bard. A guilded bard or one that groups regularly with friends (or guildies) is great.
<br />

<br />
IMO you have a fun class to play, as far as options, at least as many as a bard (non-raiding). Its something different but but a no more powerful PC than your BL.
<br />

<br />
Certainly solo, I think the BL has more options.
<br />

<br />
LFG times have increased for all classes (that normally do pick up groups) on my server. My RL friend has a 55 BL and has the same problems (on The Rathe) as you and he is in a reasonable sized Mid Level guild.
<br />

<br />
I guess I'm telling you I am someone who quite playing (his now unguilded) bard to box other classes.
<br />

<br />
Pulling LDoN's for elemental plus groups who can kill nearly faster than I can pull (or drawing a group of idiots) just isn't as fun for me as it once was.  Seems like the pick up groups I do always have one or more elementals (non MT type) that causes aggro to bounce all over the place.
<br />

<br />
I am sure strong guild bards have a different view than me.</span></td>
