			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question on Bard alt<a name="69073"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 5 04 2:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, bards that can pull WoS do get groups a lot easier, I usually get random group requests within minutes of logging in simply because I am a 66 bard located in PoK (obviously not grouped, lol) even though I am not flagged LFG.  The problem is you are still dealing with pick-up groups.  I RARELY do pick-up groups for these reasons, fortunately I have a solid core group in my guild... however things to combat this kind of problem are to take control of your groups.
<br />

<br />
Make sure YOU are finding replacements when people have to leave, give direction when people seem clueless, squash/solve arguements between group members... groups will survive longer this way.  Be the ML if you can also, if you are holding all the loot and want to keep fighting not as many people will just bail.
<br />

<br />
Aside from how to make a pick-up group work better, yes, a bard can get a group easier, and yes they can be GREAT fun.  My tips are work on hps and charisma so you can survive, and so your lulls don't get critical agro.  With that, and experience, you can be a great puller.  The items you listed can be helpfull, the FT3 probably being more so if you get fading memories, less so until then, but none are required.  I don't have my epic, or a LoTH, or ornate boots... I actually have decided not to get them because they don't have very good stats/hps/ac on them (the boots) and the LoTH doesn't have a very high string mod on it, do BB hard LDoNs when you reach 65 to get the lute from there (2.6 mod), the haste is neat, but not really needed.  The epic takes so much time you could do LDoNs and WoS to get similar instrument mods in the same amount of time, with less headache, and MUCH more xp/loot.
<br />

<br />
So I recommend leveling and getting WoS and hard LDoN groups.  Group to level though so you can learn how to pull, otherwise when you get to the WoS or hard LDoNs you will just die a LOT more than you need to, and get very frustrated with your bard.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
