				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question on Bard alt<a name="69137"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 7 04 12:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a 67 SK and a 58 bard alt that I like to play. You didn't mention what lvl your bard alt is, and that would definitely affect my response. These are the pro's and con's that I've come across (on the Lanys server).
<br />

<br />
Pro's:
<br />
1) No one asks my hp's/AC as a bard.
<br />
2) Can fulfill a variety of group functions, so it's much easier to &quot;make&quot; pick up groups successful.
<br />

<br />
Con's:
<br />
1) It is tough to find groups. It seems like there are so few people below lvl 65 that competition for groups is high. And that's if you can find enough people on at suitable lvls to make a group.
<br />
2) I can see that future lvling will take awhile. PreOoW, you could get in groups with higher lvl/more progressed tanks. It doesn't seem to be that way now.
<br />
3) Forget soloing as a way to effectively get exp.
<br />
4) There is limited CC below lvl 62, as mezzes don't keep up with your lvl.
<br />

<br />
I enjoy playing my bard and will continue to do so, but I'm willing to go through a slow grind to lvl.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Panben
<br />
</span></td>
