				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question on Bard alt<a name="69438"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 10 04 11:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I personally will not play any class where equipment is extremely important and noticable.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
That&#180;s my kind of thinking also. I started my EQ life with casters, chanter, mage and necro, and back then casters got away with crappy gear. I would get utterly fustrated if I needed better gear and weapons every so and so level in order to be effective in groups.
<br />

<br />
However, with my bard I started to feel the need for better gear at around 30, and while I still could get around with it, with fear kiting, or any other form of kiting, my defense skills started to fall behind a lot. Heck, it took a lot of LDoN ripostes to max my Defense skill, I was 150 skill points behind, LOL. 
<br />

<br />
Then when bard was 36, with the help of a smither friend I farmed the components required with my chanter, and got a full set of Hurricane Plate done by the time bard was 46. And that was cool, and I was happy for a while, but then LDoN came about and I got 252 Defense skill and a full set of EF bard armor to stick some FT augments on it.
<br />

<br />
Now with OOW, armor getting is much easier, I still wear half of the EF LDoN armor for my dodge mod and the FTs, and the rest is either OOW, KT or MPG (the leggings with FT2 are pretty sweet).
<br />

<br />
But all along thru the armor upgrading process, a need kept creeping up as levels, AAs and time passed by, instrument and singing mods. Thus ended up getting my epic and I am very happy with it. I recommend you to do the epic, it is not all that hard at all. There are a few pains, but most of it is pretty easy. Trak and Mr. Old were my pains, scales... you can buy them if need to.
<br />

<br />
Play the classes you like most, if you like bard and getting tired of LFGing with BL, go for it. When someone on my group leaves, and they say &quot;want a BL?&quot; it is REALLY pretty hard to say no. BLs are slow, mana regen, HP buffes, DPS, and some tank here and there, pretty well rounded if you ask me. You shouldn&#180;t get much problems with BL LFGing, but I know nothing about it, all I know is that I always say yes to &quot;want a BL replacement?&quot; Bear in mind than with EQ2 live, as of yesterday, all servers will get slow for a while...
<br />

<br />
Oh, and yesterday I tanked an elite Ukun in MPG (Odium PH - the nasty kind that procs the 850 AE claw thing alot more than the others). Tank died at 75%, BL got agro, died in like 1 sec, I got bish slapped to 40%, stepped back, necro pet got agro, clicked my AA Defensive disc (Rank 1 only), got back in for more smacking treatment (dodge all disc was down from getting snared on a pull before by another dog), cleric spammed heals, dog died, and then we all laught at the warrior (guildie).
<br />

<br />
I did this with 7400HPs and 1500AC, as my bard is an alt with ZERO raid items (LR5 and ID5. Will get level 10 for both as soon as I get level 70, in half a level). 
<br />

<br />
Yet, it is still nice to have some somewhat decent gear, specially when pulling in MPG, with nocs rampaging you for 1011 x 3 plus 2 650 procs when they get lucky.</span></td>
